According to the non-profit organization Iran Human Rights, on November 19, 2022, at least 378 people were killed, 43 of them were minors under 18, due to the government's intervention in the protests, where tear gas and gunfire were used. Julie Ledru stars in the film as Julia. She is a young woman who lives in social housing and has a bad relationship with her mother. She loves motocross and tries to get a chance to participate in the sport by pretending to be a customer on online shopping websites. She uses this as a way to take bikes out for test rides.
